## Package (CRITICAL)

```bash
npm install @fhevm/solidity @zama-fhe/relayer-sdk @openzeppelin/contracts
```

Import pattern for every FHEVM contract:
```solidity
import "@fhevm/solidity/lib/FHE.sol";
import "@fhevm/solidity/config/ZamaConfig.sol";

contract MyContract is ZamaEthereumConfig {
    // ...
}
```

NEVER import from `fhevm-solidity` ‚Äî that package is archived (June 2025).

## Types

Usable types in v0.11.1:
```
euint8 euint16 euint32 euint64 euint128 euint160 euint256
ebool eaddress
externalEuint8..externalEuint256 (ZKPoK inputs)
```

`eint` and `ebytes` are declared as types but have no FHE operations ‚Äî do not use.
`euint256` supports only: `eq`, `ne`, `and`, `or`, `xor`, `select` ‚Äî no arithmetic.

## ACL Pattern

Every stored handle needs explicit permissions:
```solidity
euint64 private encryptedBalance;

function store(externalEuint64 inp, bytes calldata proof) external {
    euint64 val = FHE.fromExternal(inp, proof);
    encryptedBalance = val;
    FHE.allowThis(val);          // required: contract access
    FHE.allow(val, msg.sender);  // required: user access
}
```

## ZKPoK Input Pattern

```solidity
// Correct: validate with ZKPoK proof
function transfer(address to, externalEuint64 encAmt, bytes calldata proof) external {
    euint64 amount = FHE.fromExternal(encAmt, proof);
    // use amount
}

// WRONG: never accept raw uint64
function transfer(address to, uint64 rawAmount) external { ... } // AP-007
```

